  When a prior batch/run produced an unparseable or malformed completion, `parse_verdict` records the cell as `ABSENT`; passing those parsed results back via `existing` causes this branch to skip the key permanently. In that scenario the documented resilience behavior (“ABSENT ... re-attempted on resume”) is broken, leaving dead cells excluded from the denominator or causing all-ABSENT metrics to fail instead of being re-judged.
